<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B59EE3AB6A2ECDDA" bold="true" box="[160,375,140,166]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Geographic range</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B07431609FFE6B59EE396693CCC72" blockId="31.[160,1155,140,270]" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01609FFE6B59EE3966AD2CDB5" box="[160,395,177,201]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nimihil">
<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B59EE3966AD2CDB5" box="[160,395,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Monomorium nimihil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="3B5C0D1E1609FFE6B4A7E39668E6CD90" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3762058326" country="Socotra Island" latitude="12.616667" location="Wadi Daneghan" longLatPrecision="1" longitude="54.066666" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" specimenCount="1">
is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="548FB9E11609FFE6B7FFE39669AACDB5" box="[705,755,177,201]" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<location id="8EEB51981609FFE6B65CE3966F46CDB5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039DB655160BFFE6B4A2E6A7689DCCE5:8EEB51981609FFE6B65CE3966F46CDB5" box="[866,1055,177,201]" country="Socotra Island" latitude="12.616667" longLatPrecision="1" longitude="54.066666" name="Wadi Daneghan" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Wadi Daneghan</location>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D31609FFE6B110E3966BBCCD90" name="Socotra Island" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Socotra Island</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE0061841609FFE6B5D1E3F36A26CD90" box="[239,383,212,236]" degrees="12.616667" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" precision="1" value="12.616667">12.616667°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE0061841609FFE6B4B7E3F3694DCD90" box="[393,532,212,236]" degrees="54.066667" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" precision="1" value="54.066666">54.066667°E</geoCoordinate>
, and therefore is considered endemic
</materialsCitation>
. No new material was collected during the present study.
</paragraph>
