<subSubSection id="C32E54C81609FFE6B59EE21D689DCCE5" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8B07431609FFE6B59EE21D694CCC28" blockId="31.[160,1156,314,409]" box="[160,533,314,340]" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B59EE21D694CCC28" bold="true" box="[160,533,314,340]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Ecological and biological notes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B07431609FFE6B59EE279689DCCE5" blockId="31.[160,1156,314,409]" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">
The species was reported from leaf litter under a fig tree, mostly 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01609FFE6B687E2796A17CCE5" authority="(Vahl)" baseAuthorityName="Vahl" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="cordata" variety="salicifolia">
<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B687E2796F16CC0A" box="[953,1103,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">Ficus cordata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B940DB511609FFE6B59EE2A66A5CCCE5" box="[160,261,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="347">salicifolia</emphasis>
(Vahl)
</taxonomicName>
next to a permanent stream (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB21609FFE6B799E2A668EECCE5" author="Collingwood CA &amp; Pohl H &amp; Guesten R &amp; Wranik W &amp; Van Harten A" box="[679,951,385,409]" pageId="31" pageNumber="347" pagination="473 - 495" refId="ref18239" refString="Collingwood CA, Pohl H, Guesten R, Wranik W, Van Harten A. 2004. The ants (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of the Socotra Archipelago. Fauna of Arabia. 20: 473 - 495." type="journal article" year="2004">Collingwood et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
